ce:section.ce:para:
An overview of the TiCl3 doped sample after one complete desorption (Fig. 3
) indicates that particles have smooth shapes (from irregular to spherical) and sizes ranging from about 0.5 to 11μm. Analysis of the TiCl3 doped NaAlH4 microstructure reveals the variety of the particles shape as well as the drastic change which occur at different stages of desorption and absorption of hydrogen. Fig. 4
 displays the microstructure as well as the elemental maps of Al, Na, Cl and Ti of particles in the (bm), (dd) and (da) state. After ball milling (bm) the particles have a dense structure whereas during desorption (dd) and during the absorption (da) of hydrogen the structure of the particles becomes porous with pores randomly distributed in the particle. Pores are characterized by a curved interface of different shape embedded in the matrix and their sizes vary from about 20nm to 7μm. Elemental mapping of the particles confirms the dense structure in the ball-milled state. Additionally, in the different stages of the decomposition and reloading reaction, elemental maps taken at lower resolution exhibit a uniform distribution of Al, Na, Cl and Ti everywhere except in the pores. At this scale, no lack of correlation between different elements was detected.

The scanning electron micrograph of the Ti cluster material as synthesized (Fig. 7
) reveals that particles have different shape (most of them with facets) with size ranging from about 8 to 60μm. SEM micrographs of doped alanate samples (bm), (dd) and (da) as well as the enlargement of some specific particles (Fig. 8
) reveal the presence of two types of particles at the different stages of the reaction. Particles on the one hand coalesce to form aggregates of size ranging from about 40 to 160μm which are characterized by the presence of numerous pores. The tendency to form aggregates increases from the ball-milled state to the absorbed one. On the other hand, spheroidical shaped particles (without facets) of diameters ranging from about 8 to 50μm are also found. These particles do not have any pores and EDX analysis performed on them reveals the presence of Na, Al and Ti. Similarly, to the TiCl3 doped alanate some particles seemed not to take part in the reaction.
